name: Montreat Conference Center
directions: single-stall restroom on the second floor of the inn in the lobby. When you go in and you are facing the front desk, turn left and go up the stairs to the lobby (not the reading room). There is a single-occupancy gender neutral bathroom on the left-hand side of the room.
comment: It's 10 minutes out of the way from Black Mountain but all of the facilities owned by PCUSA (prebyterian church united states of america) are safe zones and most employees have undertaken training to make the area a safe place. Particular places that are safe: the inn, the office buildings, the art/pottery building, anderson auditorium, and the huck/huckleberry cafe. The Inn has a neutral single-stall bathroom on the second floor in the lobby.

name: Eastern Florida State College
directions: There's two single stalled gender neutral restrooms on each of the three floors of Building 3! Building 3 is the UCF building on campus, and is right across from the library.

name: middle georgia state university
directions: on the first floor of walker hall, next to the women's bathroom.
comment: there are guest parking spots out front, if you aren't a student make sure you find one or you'll be ticketed!

name: Starbucks
directions: Near back entrance
comment: Requires 5-digit code; baristas will generally tell it to you no questions asked. Code changes every month or two.

name: Palantir Technologies
directions: Second floor by the rear stairwell.
comment: Private business restroom.

name: Target
directions: Front of store, behind aisles A42 & A44, to the right of the pharmacy

name: Target
directions: Front of store, behind aisles A42 & A44, to the right of the pharmacy

name: The Coffee Bean and Tea Leaf
directions: Next to the rear entrance

name: Bed Bath & Beyond
directions: Hallway to left immediately after entrance vestibule

name: Peace Harbor Rehabilitation and Wellness
directions: In front lobby, patient waiting area
comment: Staff are friendly, I think it wouldn't be even thought about if someone came in ton quickly use the restroom.

name: VisualEyes Optometrists
comment: Open to public, but try to look like a possible customer

name: Upper Canada Mall
directions: Second floor, just outside of the food court
comment: Labeled as a "family washroom". Only has 2 stalls, but they have full size locking doors and are very spacious and accessible.

name: Micky's Irish Pub
directions: The restrooms are downstairs. On the right hand side is the "men's restroom", but it's a single stall and locks whereas the other bathroom has two stalls.
comment: Typically it's "customers only", but if you just walk in and go downstairs you may get some funny looks, but no one will stop you or make you feel uncomfortable.

name: Renton Library
comment: There are gendered multi stall restrooms, but there is also a family restroom that's single stall and anyone can use. You do have to ask for the key at the front desk

name: Telegraph Corner
directions: First floor outside of family Medicine office
comment: Do not need to be a customer as long as the building is open.

name: Soapstone market
directions: Back left corner of the market

name: Kirkwood United Methodist Church
directions: In cry room in lounge outside sanctuary
comment: Open during regular church hours: 8am - 8pm, Tues/Wed/Thurs/Sat/Sun; 8am-4:30pm, Mon & Fri

name: Valley library: OSU
directions: First floor of library, take a left before the printers. In hallway across from women's bathroom. Next to water fountain.
comment: I believe this restroom is labeled as a "family" bathroom. I believe it is single stall, but I do not think you can lock the door to get into the bathroom itself.

name: Khaos Company Theatre
comment: You probably have to be a customer.

name: Khaos Company Theatre
comment: You probably have to be a customer.

name: Walmart Supercentee
directions: At the front of the store, to the right of the customer service desk
comment: Labeled as a "family washroom"

name: Teaism
directions: First floor, to the left of the kitchen

name: The Monument Cafe
directions: Back of the restaurant, to your right as you enter.
comment: There are 4 single-occupancy unisex restrooms available.

name: Lebanese Taverna
comment: Shared sink area separated from restaurant by a curtain, multiple unisex single person stalls. Need to be a paying customer.

name: Riverviews Artspace
directions: All public floors. Ground, first, and second.
comment: The building auto locks after 8pm. Only open to the public between 8am and 8pm.

name: Shift Coffee
comment: Open 7AM to 7PM

name: Abbey Coffee Company
directions: It's in a little nook to the left of the ordering counter.

name: Starbucks
directions: Just a few feet from the register

name: King's Place Mall
directions: In the hallway that leads to Shopper's Drug Mart
comment: It is a single toilet washroom, for all/no gender as well as the differently abled.

name: Marcus Point Cinema
directions: To the left behind concession stand, to the left down long hallway across from #11.
comment: You have to be a paying customer for theatre bathrooms. Don't necessarily have to be a customer to use bar bathrooms.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back, past the walk up window.
comment: There is a code you have to get (so probably have to be a paying customer).

name: Marcus Point Cinema
directions: Back left of Take 5 Lounge
comment: Don't have to be a paying customer to use bar bathrooms.

name: Pet food express
directions: Right past the register which is in the middle of the store
comment: You don't need to be a customer, there are two unisex bathrooms and they are clean and the staff is very kind and a lot of them are queer

name: Bradbury-Sullivan LGBT Center
directions: up the stairs past the books, second door on the left side of the big room

name: Kroger
directions: On the left side of the store when you are coming in, between the icecream coolers and the pharmacy.

name: Harvard Law School Lewis Hall
directions: 3rd floor (main floor/lobby level is 2nd floor) next to elevator
comment: single use gender neutral bathroom

name: Bourgeois Pig Cafe
directions: One bathroom on the left side (at the back, first floor) and two bathrooms on the right side (at the back and one at the top of the stairs)
comment: All 3 restrooms are gender neutral/single stall

name: Woolworths Supermarket
directions: Near the trolley bay inside
comment: Accesible without having to purcahse anything. May be locked if recently vandalised.

name: Taco Bell
comment: They're gendered single stall but they generally don't care which one you use.

name: Starbucks
directions: Right next to the West entrance
comment: Feel free to say "hi" if I'm working! Ask for "Fliss" :P

name: Tharpa Choeling Wellington Buddhist Centre
directions: At the rear of the property
comment: We are open Saturday, Sunday and Monday 1-4pm, there are two restrooms, one with access for people with ability issues. Our volunteers are helpful and respectful, please come to us with any needs.

name: The Elbow Room
directions: Past the counter on the right
comment: Depends on who's working there at the time but they might make you buy something first. They're sometimes rude to people (especially kids/teens) but in general you should be okay. Never experienced homophobia/transphobia from the staff.

name: Jenny K
directions: All the way in the back, purple door
comment: You do not have to be a customer

name: Lincoln Square
directions: Back of the dining room
comment: Not sure if it is customers only

name: Blue Danube Coffee House
directions: Past the counter and down the hall. The bathroom is on the left after the kitchen and just before the back door.
comment: The people who work here are all lovely and won't make you pretend you're a customer, but be a good egg and buy a coffee if you can.

name: The Flushing A
comment: Generally you don't have to purchase anything

name: Drama Book Shop
comment: May or may not be accessible, I can't remember

name: Purple Kow
comment: You have to ask for a key at the counter but they will almost always give it to you even if you are not a customer

name: Centennial Sportsplex
directions: I know that there's one next to the locker rooms in the swimming pool area (pool is right of the main entrance, bathrooms/locker rooms are across from the stands). i'm pretty sure there isn't a unisex one in the main lobby though and I'm not sure about the ice rink.
comment: The pool opens at 6am but I'm not sure of the closing times, they're subject to change depending on what events the facility is hosting at the time. There is also a fee in the front lobby for the pool though, the fees vary on age. For college students (w/ student I.D.) it's 7.00$ and the same for Seniors 62 and over, ages 5–17, Disabled, and Active Military. It's 8$ for adults ages 18–61.

name: Ruloff's
directions: On the first floor in the back

name: Vidler's 5 & 10
directions: In the hallway by the card and gift shops.
comment: There are two single restrooms.  They are both gender neutral.  You don't even have to pretend you're a paying customer.  It's a tourist destination, they're not ever gonna police the restrooms for any reason.

name: Clark Hall
directions: Second floor in the atrium

name: 48 Main Street/Meredith Whole Living Center
directions: First floor rest room accessible through side ramp and down hallway. All second floor restrooms gender neutral and safe spaces.
comment: Accessible gender neutral restroom on first floor of building. Meredith Whole Living Center on second floor has gender neutral bathroom and is a safe space.

name: Boudin Bakery
directions: 2 unisex/handicapped accessible bathrooms. In the back past the registers, to the left.
comment: This is more of a restaurant than just a bakery. You don't need a key or anything for the rest rooms.

name: Starbucks
directions: Two single-stall accessible restrooms in the back, one closer to the counter and another opposite it, in the far back corner from the door.
comment: They don't mind non-customers as long as you're subtle and respectful about it.

name: Chester County Library
directions: On the second floor next to the Struble Room

name: Crawford Complex Lobby, MNSU Campus
directions: One on either side of the dorm entryway. If entering from the driveup area, go right, then left into the open area with a service desk. That entrance is the dorm entryway. If entering from the main doors, walk to the entryway, and they will be on either side of you. They are labled as gender neutral.

name: Ale and witch
directions: When facing the bar, it's to the left.

name: Berkeley Law School
directions: Go in the entrance on Bancroft, closest to Piedmont. Go in building, walk all the way down the hall, turn left, then walk down hall and turn right, walk to end of this hall. Take elevator D to 4th floor. Two bathrooms right outside of the exit from Elevator D.
comment: There are probably others here at Boalt - these are just the only two I can think of.

name: Argo tea
directions: Make a purchase, door lock code is on receipt.

name: Target
directions: Next to pharmacy

name: Bismarck Airport
directions: Departures area near escalators.
comment: Marked as"Family Accessible"

name: Extended Stay America
directions: Through the lobby, to the right, next to the water fountain.
comment: Just walk in like you belong.

name: Century Cinemas at Del Monte Center
directions: On the left side of the theater, across from the girls restroom
comment: Also helpful for guys if your movie happens to be playing on the left side of the theater!

name: Glen Ellyn public library
directions: Second floor

name: Kroger
directions: By the pharmacy.  Gender neutral restroom.

name: Family Farms Market
directions: When facing the bar area, the bathrooms are down a short hallway to the left

name: Soup Peddler Real Food & Juice Bar
Rice University
directions: Lovett Hall 2nd floor, entrance C.  Unisex restroom, unmarked door on left after you go upstairs.
comment: If you're going to the admissions office it's up the stairs.  They're working on getting the sign back up.

name: Shakertin's
directions: Straight ahead after going in the main door. (Impossible to miss; giant sign on the wall.)
comment: Not sure about handicap accessibility.

name: Spicewood Springs Public Library
comment: All four restrooms are single occupant/not labeled for any gender.

name: Great Clips
directions: In the back on the left

name: Gayles Perks
directions: The people there will give you instructions if asked, but it's all the way in the back through the kitchen. It's a single stall unisex restroom
comment: I've seen people come in just to use the restroom, although I would recommend getting a drink. Their drinks are fairly inexpensive and I would really recommend them :)

name: UGA Gilbert Hall
directions: Enter the doors across from Herty Field and walk down the hallway to the right. The bathroom is on the left hand side of the hallway.

name: Tacos & Tattoos
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Rice Palace
directions: Down the hallway to the left of counter, turn right

name: Sorrell Custom Boots
comment: This is my mother's shop. She's a bootmaker but will show customers around the place because it is very cool. If you absolutely need a restroom in Guthrie and the library isn't an option for some reason, you can come into my mom's shop and ask to use her bathroom. There is a public bathroom down the hall, she just doesn't get many walk-in customers so it doesn't see much use, but this bathroom is available. My mom is very friendly and LGBT+ accepting, guaranteed by this agender asexual lesbian.

name: UGA Main Library
directions: On the third floor in the small hallway right across from the Digital Humanities Lab

name: SongBird Studios
directions: After you walk in, in the waiting area there's a hallway. It's at the very beginning of that hallway to the right.
comment: It's a place for vocal lessons so you won't constantly be able to use it but if you need to use the bathroom the lady is really nice and she'll probably understand. Or, you can act interested in lessons and then ask to use the restroom.
